[108.979215, "o", "                                                         \u001b[1;4mClick Repository Onboarding Document\u001b[0m                                                         \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mWhat this repo actually does\u001b[0m                                                                                                                          \r\n\r\nClick is a Python library for creating command-line interfaces (CLIs). It provides a decorator-based API that makes it easy to build complex          \r\ncommand-line tools with options, arguments, subcommands, and rich features like help generation, input validation, and shell completion.              \r\n\r\nThe library transforms Python functions into CLI commands using decorators like \u001b[1;36;40m@click.command()\u001b[0m and \u001b[1;36;40m@click.option()\u001b[0m. It handles argument parsing,    \r\ntype conversion, help text generation, and error handling automatically.                                                                              \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mHow to run it locally\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                 \r\n\r\nBased on the project structure, this appears to be a library (not a standalone application). To work with it:                                         \r\n\r\n\u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0mClone the repository                                                                                                                               \r\n\u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0mInstall in development mode: \u001b[1;36;40mpip install -e .\u001b[0m                                                                                                      \r\n\u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0mRun tests: \u001b[1;36;40mpython -m pytest tests/\u001b[0m                                                                                                                 \r\n\u001b[36m 4 \u001b[0mTry examples: \u001b[1;36;40mcd examples/inout && python inout.py --help\u001b[0m                                                                                          \r\n\r\nThe main package is in \u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/\u001b[0m and follows modern Python packaging standar"]
[108.979543, "o", "ds with \u001b[1;36;40mpyproject.toml\u001b[0m.                                                  \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mArchitecture: how the pieces connect\u001b[0m                                                                                                                  \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mCore Architecture:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mcore.py\u001b[0m - Central classes: \u001b[1;36;40mCommand\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mGroup\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mOption\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mArgument\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mContext\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mParameter\u001b[0m                                                                    \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mdecorators.py\u001b[0m - User-facing decorators (\u001b[1;36;40m@command\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40m@option\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40m@argument\u001b[0m)                                                                              \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mparser.py\u001b[0m - Command-line argument parsing logic                                                                                                    \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mtypes.py\u001b[0m - Parameter type system with validation and conversion                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mKey Flow:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                             \r\n\r\n\u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0mDecorators create \u001b[1;36;40mCommand\u001b[0m/\u001b[1;36;40mGroup\u001b[0m objects with attached \u001b[1;36;40mParameter\u001b[0m instances                                                                          \r\n\u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mContext\u001b[0m objects carry state through command execution                                                                                              \r\n\u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mParser\u001b[0m handles the actual CLI argument parsing                                                                                                     \r\n\u001b[36m 4 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mParamType\u001b[0m subclasses convert and validate string inputs to Python types                                                                            \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mCommand Structure:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mCommands can be standalone or grouped into hierarchies                                                                                             \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mGroups can dynamically load subcommands (see \u001b[1;36;40mComplexCLI\u001b[0m example)                                                                                   \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mContext objects enable data sharing between parent and child commands                                                                              \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mCore files to read first (with one-line explanations)\u001b[0m                                                                                                 \r\n\r\n\u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/__init__.py\u001b[0m - Main API surface, shows all exported functionality                                                                         \r\n\u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/decorators.py\u001b[0m - Core decorators that users interact with most                                                                            \r\n\u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/core.py\u001b[0m - Command, Group, and Parameter class definitions                                                                                \r\n\u001b[36m 4 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/types.py\u001b[0m - Type system for parameter validation and conversion                                                                           \r\n\u001b[36m 5 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mexamples/complex/complex/cli.py\u001b[0m - Real example showing advanced patterns                                                                           \r\n\u001b[36m 6 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/parser.py\u001b[0m - Low-level argument parsing implementation                                                                                    \r\n\u001b[36m 7 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/utils.py\u001b[0m - Utility functions like \u001b[1;"]
[108.979938, "o", "36;40mecho()\u001b[0m for output                                                                                      \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mKey patterns and conventions\u001b[0m                                                                                                                          \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mDecorator Chaining:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                   \r\n\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                                      \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;148;48;5;235m@click\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;204;48;5;235m.\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mcommand\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m(\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m)\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                    \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;148;48;5;235m@click\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;204;48;5;235m.\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235moption\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m(\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m--count\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m,\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mdefault\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;204;48;5;235m=\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;141;48;5;235m1\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m,\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mhelp\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;204;48;5;235m=\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235mNumber of greetings.\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m)\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                    \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;148;48;5;235m@click\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;204;48;5;235m.\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235margument\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m(\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235mname\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m)\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                             \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;81;48;5;235mdef\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;148;48;5;235mhello\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m(\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mcount\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m,\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mname\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m)\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m:\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                             \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m    \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;244;48;5;235m# Function parameters match decorator names\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                     \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                                      \u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mContext Passing:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                      \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40m@pass_context\u001b[0m gives access to the Click context                                                                                                    \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mpass_environment = click.make_pass_decorator(Environment, ensure=True)\u001b[0m creates custom context decorators                                           \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mDynamic Command Loading:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mInherit from \u001b[1;36;40mclick.Group\u001b[0m and override \u001b[1;36;40mlist_commands()\u001b[0m/\u001b[1;36;40mget_command()\u001b[0m                                                                                \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mCommand files follow \u001b[1;36;40mcmd_*.py\u001b[0m naming convention                                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mType System:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                          \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mBuilt-in types: "]
[108.980407, "o", "\u001b[1;36;40mINT\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mFLOAT\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mSTRING\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mChoice\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mPath\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mFile\u001b[0m                                                                                             \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mCustom types inherit from \u001b[1;36;40mParamType\u001b[0m and implement \u001b[1;36;40mconvert()\u001b[0m                                                                                        \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mEnvironment Variables:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mAuto-prefixed with \u001b[1;36;40mCONTEXT_SETTINGS = dict(auto_envvar_prefix=\"MYAPP\")\u001b[0m                                                                             \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mOptions automatically map to env vars like \u001b[1;36;40mMYAPP_COUNT\u001b[0m                                                                                             \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mWhat is undocumented or surprising\u001b[0m                                                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mContext State Management:\u001b[0m The \u001b[1;36;40mEnvironment\u001b[0m class pattern in examples shows how to maintain application state across commands, but this isn't obvious\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0mfrom the main API                                                                                                                                  \r\n\u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mDynamic Command Discovery:\u001b[0m The \u001b[1;36;40mComplexCLI\u001b[0m example shows sophisticated runtime command loading that's more powerful than the basic decorator        \r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0mapproach                                                                                                                                           \r\n\u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mParameter Name Mapping:\u001b[0m Function parameter names must exactly match decorator option/argument names - there's no automatic conversion              \r\n\u001b[36m 4 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mType Conversion Timing:\u001b[0m Type conversion happens during parsing, not during function execution, which affects error handling                        \r\n\u001b[36m 5 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mShell Completion:\u001b[0m The library has built-in shell completion support, but it's not prominently featured in basic examples                           \r\n\u001b[36m 6 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mFile Handling:\u001b[0m The \u001b[1;36;40mFile\u001b[0m type and \u001b[1;36;40mLazyFile\u001b[0m utility provide sophisticated file handling that goes beyond simple path strings                         \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mWhere to go next\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                      \r\n\r\n"]
[108.98068, "o", "\u001b[1mFor New Contributors:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                 \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mStart with \u001b[1;36;40mtests/\u001b[0m to understand expected behavior                                                                                                  \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mLook at \u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/testing.py\u001b[0m for the test CLI runner utilities                                                                                     \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mCheck \u001b[1;36;40mexamples/\u001b[0m for real-world usage patterns                                                                                                      \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mFor Users Learning the Library:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                       \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mBegin with simple examples in \u001b[1;36;40mexamples/\u001b[0m                                                                                                            \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mRead through the decorator implementations in \u001b[1;36;40mdecorators.py\u001b[0m                                                                                        \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mStudy the \u001b[1;36;40mComplexCLI\u001b[0m example for advanced multi-command applications                                                                               \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mFor Advanced Usage:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                   \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mExplore custom \u001b[1;36;40mParamType\u001b[0m implementations in \u001b[1;36;40mtypes.py\u001b[0m                                                                                               \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mLook at the formatting system in \u001b[1;36;40mformatting.py\u001b[0m                                                                                                     \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mStudy the terminal utilities in \u001b[1;36;40mtermui.py\u001b[0m for rich CLI features                                                                                    \r\n\r\nThe codebase is well-structured and follows clear separation of concerns, making it relatively easy to understand the flow from user-facing decorators\r\ndown to the core parsing and execution logic.                                                                                                         \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mREADME vs reality\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \r\n\r\n\u001b[1;35mWhat the source code reveals that the README doesn't mention\u001b[0m                                                                                          \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mRich type system with validation\u001b[0m: The codebase includes sophisticated parameter types (\u001b[1;36;40mPath\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mFile\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mChoice\u001b[0m, etc.) with built-in validation and      \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mconversion that goes far beyond simple string arguments                                                                                            \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mContext system for state management\u001b[0m: The \u001b[1;36;40mContext\u001b[0m class and \u001b[1;36;40m@pass_context\u001b[0m decorator enable complex state sharing between commands, but this pattern \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mis completely absent from the README                                                                                                               \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mShell completion support\u001b[0m: Built-in shell completion functionality exists in the codebase but isn't mentioned as a feature                          \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mDynamic command loading capabilities\u001b[0m: The parser supports runtime command discovery through \u001b[1;36;40mlist_commands()\u001b[0m/\u001b[1;36;40mget_command()\u001b[0m overrides, enabling      \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mplugin-like architectures                                                                                                                          \r\n\r\n\u001b[1;35mWhat the README oversimplifies or skips\u001b[0m                                                           "]
[108.981086, "o", "                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mEnvironment variable integration\u001b[0m: The README doesn't mention that Click automatically maps options to environment variables with configurable      \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mprefixes (via \u001b[1;36;40mauto_envvar_prefix\u001b[0m)                                                                                                                  \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mTesting infrastructure\u001b[0m: The library includes \u001b[1;36;40mclick.testing.CliRunner\u001b[0m for testing CLI applications, which is crucial for development but not        \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mhighlighted                                                                                                                                        \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mTerminal utilities\u001b[0m: The \u001b[1;36;40mtermui.py\u001b[0m module provides progress bars, prompts, and other rich terminal features that aren't reflected in the simple     \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mexample                                                                                                                                            \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mParameter naming constraints\u001b[0m: The README example doesn't reveal that function parameter names must exactly match decorator option/argument names - \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mthere's no automatic conversion between formats like \u001b[1;36;40m--my-option\u001b[0m and \u001b[1;36;40mmy_option\u001b[0m                                                                     \r\n"]
[108.984679, "o", "\r\n\u001b[32mSaved to \u001b[0m\u001b[32m/tmp/\u001b[0m\u001b[32mdemo-out.md\u001b[0m\r\n"]
